        "content": "type: sheet\napp_id: sheets\nskill_id: sheet\ntable: \"| Dimension | Option A: Local-Only | Option B: Zero-Retention Cloud | Option C: Hybrid Local/Cloud |\\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\\n| **Security & Compliance Trust** | **Absolute** (Easiest to sell to paranoid buyers; no cloud vector). | **High** (Requires trusting zero-knowledge cryptography and vendor guarantees). | **Moderate-High** (Requires deep trust in local data sanitization/PII stripping). |\\n| **Hardware / Performance** | **Dependent on user's machine** (Requires Apple Silicon or a decent NVIDIA GPU; sluggish on older laptops). | **Blazing Fast** (Offloaded to heavy-duty cloud GPUs; handles large context windows easily). | **Adaptive** (Fast for cloud tasks, runs local fallback for sensitive jobs). |\\n| **Infrastructure & Hosting Cost** | **Zero server inference cost** (Users pay with their own compute). | **High operational burn** (GPU hosting, scaling, and container management). | **Moderate** (Mixed cloud and local compute load). |\\n| **Engineering Complexity** | **High client-side complexity** (Packaging models, cross-platform hardware acceleration, local vector DBs). | **Moderate backend complexity** (Standard web app + secure enclave infrastructure). | **Very High** (Complex routing logic, sanitization classifiers, dual codebases). |\"\ntitle: \"\"\nembed_ref: sheet-bd4554\nstatus: finished\nrow_count: 4\ncol_count: 4",
